Rating: 4
Fantastic! Followed the recipe in detail, the first time. Used feta cheese imported from Greece; the grocer cut a piece from a round of cheese in a brine filled wooden barrel. Second time: used 3/4 cup of feta, left out the mint but added 18 Kalamata olives pitted and sliced thin. These were also a product of Greece and are far superior to those grown in the US. They added a nice flavour.Buying these items "in bulk" appeals to my Scottish ancestory. Great dish!

